<item>
            <title>[HIVE-3134] Drop table/index/database can result in orphaned locations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-3134</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Today when a managed table has a partition with a location which is not a subdirectory of the table&apos;s location, when the table is dropped the partition&apos;s data is not deleted from HDFS, resulting in an orphaned directory (the data exists but nothing points to it).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same applies to dropping a database with cascade and a table has a location outside the database.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it is safe to assume managed tables/partitions own the directories they point to, so we should clean these up.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
